text: Stephen Brian Wooldridge (17 October 1977 - 14 August 2017) was an Australian racing cyclist, an Olympic and four-time world champion on the track. He was born in Sydney. He was an Australian Institute of Sport scholarship holder. In 2005, Wooldridge was awarded a Medal of the Order of Australia. He was inducted into the NSW Hall of Champions in 2015. Wooldridge committed suicide on 14 August 2017 in Sydney at the age of 39. ==References== Category:1977 births Category:2017 deaths Category:Suicides in Australia Category:Olympians for Australia Category:Australian cyclists Category:Sportspeople from Sydney
